title: Cloquet Sweeps Individual LSC XC Titles
text:
Cloquet Sweeps Individual LSC XC Titles 
By Zach Schneider October 13, 2015 Updated Oct 13, 2015 at 10:48 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Cloquet's Anja Maijala and Isaac Boedigheimer swept the individual titles on Tuesday afternoon at the Lake Superior Conference (LSC) cross country championships, which were held at Far Par Golf Course in Duluth, Minn. 
Maijala spent most of the race in the lead pack, finishing in a time of 19:20.7 to edge Proctor's Annika Voss, who finished as the runner-up in a time of 19:34.2. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Boedigheimer then followed that with a win in 16:23.9, staving off several challengers throughout the course. One of them was from Ashland's Maury Miller, who finished as the runner-up in 16:29.6. 
The Ashland girls successfully defended their team title from 2014 with a low score of 51, while the Cloquet boys also took home the team honor with a score of 27.
